  "text": "Summary. An understanding of MTX's distribution and metabolism can help guide rational therapy with this drug. CLEARANCE MTX clearance decreases by a factor of approximately three as age increases from 7 to 15 yr, explaining why some children require larger doses than adults [CITATION_1] . Further, both renal and metabolic MTX clearance decrease at night (by 50 and 14%, respectively), at least in children, supplying a rationale for changes in response (either ecacy or toxicity) with changes in dosing regimens [CITATION_2] .",
